Chilean Stocks: Emb. Andina, Cap, Cencosud, CMPC and Soquimich

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-04-18T19:39:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-18/chilean-stocks-cap-cencosud-empresas-cmpc-and-soquimich-fall.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 3:08 p.m. New York time.  The Ipsa index fell 0.6 percent to 4,643.95.  Cap SA (CAP)   retreated 1 percent to 24,100 pesos, its
second day of losses. Chile’s largest steel producer and iron
miner fell as base metal prices declined after  China  announced
it would increase bank reserve requirements to stem inflation.  Cencosud SA (CENCOSUD CC) fell 0.4 percent to 3,493.3
pesos. Chile’s largest retailer by sales will experience
negative pressure on its stock after it announced plans for a $2
billion capital increase, without providing details about the
use of the funds, timing and steps of the transaction, Banco
Santander SA wrote in an e-mailed note to clients today.  Embotelladora Andina SA (AKO/A)   gained 0.6 percent to
2,250 pesos. Chile’s largest Coca-Cola bottler plans to invest
$250 million this year in its operations in Chile, Brazil and
 Argentina .  Empresas CMPC SA (CMPC)   rose 0.1 percent to 23,730
pesos. Chile’s second-largest pulp exporter was raised to
“hold” from “sell” at Banchile-Citi, the joint research
department of local lender Banco de Chile and Citigroup Inc.
Banchile-Citi said it continues to favor Brazilian pulp
producers over Chileans.  Soc. Quimica y Minera de Chile SA (SQM/B CC) fell 1.4
percent to 26,706 pesos, its lowest value in more than two
weeks. Chile’s largest fertilizer producer retreated in line
with global equity markets after China increased banks’ reserve
requirements and  Standard & Poor’s  revised its outlook for the
U.S. to negative from stable.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
 ethomson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
